The paper presents a method for skin lesion segmentation using a deep convolutional neural network, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of recent innovations in network architecture and training also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method to medical imaging and specifically skin lesions suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of end-to-end training and super-resolution upsampling suggests a possible fit with neural networks (cs.NE).
